<text>ENERGY GAMES:  A molecular playground
Two atoms

What is the force between two atoms? How is this related to energy?
Here are two atoms near each other. This is about the simplest possible model, but if you look closely there is a lot to learn. Before you start, guess what happens when you run this model. Here is a hint: all atoms attract each other. The blue arrows show the force on each atom. 

 

In this model, the shade of red indicates kinetic energy. Note how the kintetic energy changes as the atoms approach.

We made this model very slow, so you can observe it  carefully. Let it run for a few minutes while you examine it. If you understand the model you can answer these questions. 
      
      
      
      
      

Let&apos;s speed up the model a bit so things can get more interesting. 

